commit.message: Update parsing tests suite version
Implement new CSS syntax draft
Take care of declaration first token
Split deprecated and new functions

Stop pre-parsing declarations on {} blocks only when nested allowed

When nesting is not allowed, we should consume tokens until we meet a
semicolon. When it’s allowed, we have to stop at {} blocks to keep possibly
valid declarations after them.

Stop pre-parsing declarations after {} blocks

We don’t want to consume tokens after curly brackets as they may be a
declaration we want to keep in the tokens iterator.
Fix stupid equality test
Add nested and stop_token parameters for related functions
Fix import order
Fix long lines
Import parse_blocks_contents() in top level module
Add documentation and don’t break current behaviour
Handle nested qualified rules
Update lowest tested version on CI
Update supported versions of Python and tests
Use longer variable name to please flake8
Add favicon in documentation
